  <prompt>
    Filed 2026-05-27. Task 067 carry-over (CO-1) cataloged 24 pre-existing tsc errors in
    @spaarke/ui-components. These were verified pre-existing (not caused by R4) via stash/pop.
    Categories: React 19 RefObject initializer drift, TS 5 JSX namespace migration, Combobox
    onInput event-shape drift, misc nullability + implicit-any. Fix per the categories.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React 19 + TypeScript engineer. Bias toward correct React 19 idioms over backwards-compat
    patches. Per-error commit discipline (or per-category) — but as a sub-agent making changes
    in working tree only, just batch the changes; main session commits.
  </role>

  <goal>
    (1) `npx tsc --noEmit` on `@spaarke/ui-components` → 0 errors (down from 24). (2) No
    production-behavior change. (3) Existing tests pass. (4) NO modifications to DatasetGrid/
    GridView.tsx or DatasetGrid/ListView.tsx — those belong to task 073.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per `notes/b11-cast-inventory.md` CO-1, the 24 errors cluster into:

      A. React 19 RefObject initializer drift (~6 errors)
         - SprkChat.tsx:2190 — `RefObject&lt;HTMLDivElement | null&gt;` not assignable to `RefObject&lt;HTMLElement&gt;`
         - SprkChatInput.tsx:119, 233 — same `RefObject` nullability drift
         - Root cause: React 19's `useRef&lt;T&gt;(null)` returns `RefObject&lt;T | null&gt;` not `RefObject&lt;T&gt;`. Pre-React 19 code didn't anticipate the `| null`.
         - Fix: use `useRef&lt;T | null&gt;(null)` explicitly, OR narrow at use site, OR update consumer types to accept the nullable variant.

      B. TS 5 JSX namespace migration (~3 errors)
         - ThreePaneLayout.tsx:315 — `Cannot find namespace 'JSX'`
         - AiProgressStepper.tsx:272 — same
         - PanelSplitter.tsx:98 — same
         - Root cause: TypeScript 5+ moved JSX namespace into `'react'` module; global `JSX` namespace removed.
         - Fix: `import type { JSX } from 'react'` and use `JSX.Element` etc., OR use `React.JSX.Element`, OR use `React.ReactElement`.

      C. Combobox onInput event-shape drift (~6 errors)
         - TodoDetail.tsx:507, 508, 528 — Combobox `onInput` event-shape drift
         - DatasetGrid/ViewSelector.tsx:160 — implicit `any` parameter on Combobox handler
         - Root cause: Fluent v9's Combobox `onInput` expects `React.FormEvent&lt;HTMLInputElement&gt;`, not `React.ChangeEvent&lt;HTMLInputElement&gt;`.
         - Fix: align handler signatures with Fluent v9's `React.FormEventHandler&lt;HTMLInputElement&gt;`.

      D. Misc (~9 errors)
         - Various nullability + implicit-any drift. Investigate each individually.

      Files in scope:
      - src/components/SprkChat/SprkChat.tsx (RefObject drift)
      - src/components/SprkChat/SprkChatInput.tsx (RefObject drift)
      - src/components/ThreePaneLayout/ThreePaneLayout.tsx (JSX namespace)
      - src/components/AiProgressStepper/AiProgressStepper.tsx (JSX namespace)
      - src/components/PanelSplitter/PanelSplitter.tsx (JSX namespace)
      - src/components/TodoDetail/TodoDetail.tsx (Combobox onInput)
      - src/components/DatasetGrid/ViewSelector.tsx (Combobox onInput)
      - any other file that surfaces in the tsc output

      EXPLICITLY OUT OF SCOPE:
      - src/components/DatasetGrid/GridView.tsx — task 073's domain (hooks refactor)
      - src/components/DatasetGrid/ListView.tsx — task 073's domain (hooks refactor)
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChat.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChatInput.tsx</file>
