  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Baseline">Run `npx tsc --noEmit` in `Spaarke.UI.Components`. Capture full 24-error output. Categorize each into A (RefObject), B (JSX namespace), C (Combobox onInput), D (misc).</step>
    <step order="2" name="Fix Category B (JSX namespace)">Easiest first — add `import type { JSX } from 'react'` (or use `React.JSX.Element` inline). 3 files. Verify each compiles before moving on.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Fix Category A (RefObject)">SprkChat.tsx + SprkChatInput.tsx. Update `useRef` calls to `useRef&lt;T | null&gt;(null)`. Update consumer prop types to accept `RefObject&lt;T | null&gt;` if needed. Verify.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Fix Category C (Combobox onInput)">TodoDetail.tsx + DatasetGrid/ViewSelector.tsx. Align handlers with `React.FormEventHandler&lt;HTMLInputElement&gt;`. Read from `event.currentTarget.value`.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Fix Category D (misc)">Address remaining errors individually.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Typecheck verification">`npx tsc --noEmit` on `@spaarke/ui-components` → 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Test verification">`npm test` in `@spaarke/ui-components`. All tests pass. If a test relied on the old (broken) type signature, fix the test.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Document">Write `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/074-ui-components-tsc-fix.md` with per-category fix summary, file-by-file changes, any new errors that surfaced + how addressed.</step>
  </steps>

